						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift by one Vaḍugappiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Toṇḍaimāṇ, son of Avaiyampukkāṉ Vāṇarāyar of Murugamuchchi, of all the land which was irrigated by a well, south of the hill, stated to have been constructed by the donor himself-as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> to god Tiruvagattīśvaram-uḍaiya-nāyanār.</p>						

